atmxPortTable.name: atmxPortTable
atmxPortTable.description: A table of port layer status and parameter information for the UNI's physical interface.

atmxPortEntry.name: atmxPortEntry
atmxPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the physical layer of a UNI interface.

atmxPortSlotIndex.name: atmxPortSlotIndex
atmxPortSlotIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this hsm board slot.

atmxPortPortIndex.name: atmxPortPortIndex
atmxPortPortIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this atm submodule port.

atmxPortDescription.name: atmxPortDescription
atmxPortDescription.description: A description for this atm port.

atmxPortConnectionType.name: atmxPortConnectionType
atmxPortConnectionType.description: The connection type of this board.

atmxPortTransmissionType.name: atmxPortTransmissionType
atmxPortTransmissionType.description: The transmission type of this port. For example, for a port using the Sonet STS-3c physical layer at 155.52 Mbs, this object would have the Object Identifier value: atmxSonetSTS3c.

atmxPortMediaType.name: atmxPortMediaType
atmxPortMediaType.description: The type of media being used on this port. For example for a port using coaxial cable, the object would have the Object Identifier value: atmxMediaCoaxCable.

atmxPortOperStatus.name: atmxPortOperStatus
atmxPortOperStatus.description: The operational state (i.e., actual) of this port. The ILMI should not alarm on a physical interface for when the value of this object is outOfService(3). This capability is useful if the equipment is to be disconnected, or for troubleshooting purposes. A value of loopBack(4) indicates that a local loopback is in place.

atmxPortUniType.name: atmxPortUniType
atmxPortUniType.description: The type of the ATM UNI, either public or private.

atmxPortMaxVCCs.name: atmxPortMaxVCCs
atmxPortMaxVCCs.description: The maximum number of VCCs supported on this UNI.

atmxPortMaxVciBits.name: atmxPortMaxVciBits
atmxPortMaxVciBits.description: The number of active VCI bits on this interface.

atmxPortTxSegmentSize.name: atmxPortTxSegmentSize
atmxPortTxSegmentSize.description: The transmit segment size on this UNI. The nearest power of two less than or equal to this value will be used internally. The max memory is 512K, therefore the maximum number of channels will be 512K/internal tx seg size.

atmxPortRxSegmentSize.name: atmxPortRxSegmentSize
atmxPortRxSegmentSize.description: The receive segment size on this UNI. The nearest power of two less than or equal to this value will be used internally. The max memory is 512K, therefore the maximum number of channels will be 512K/internal rx seg size.

atmxPortTxBufferSize.name: atmxPortTxBufferSize
atmxPortTxBufferSize.description: The transmit buffer size on this UNI. The buffer size must be less than or equal to the segment size and should be greater than or equal to the maximum frame size.

atmxPortRxBufferSize.name: atmxPortRxBufferSize
atmxPortRxBufferSize.description: The receive buffer size on this UNI. The buffer size must be less than or equal to the segment size and should be greater than or equal to the maximum frame size.

atmxPortUniPortIndex.name: atmxPortUniPortIndex
atmxPortUniPortIndex.description: This object should not be implemented except as required for backward compatibility with version 2.0 of the UNI specification. This object provide a port index link to the UNI MIB

atmxPortAddress.name: atmxPortAddress
atmxPortAddress.description: This object should not be implemented except as required for backward compatibility with version 2.0 of the UNI specification. The Address Group, as defined as part of the separate Address Registration MIB should be used instead.

atmxPortSignalingVersion.name: atmxPortSignalingVersion
atmxPortSignalingVersion.description: Version of the ATM forum UNI Signaling.

atmxPortTimingMode.name: atmxPortTimingMode
atmxPortTimingMode.description: Timing mode to use. Use local timing or loop timing.

atmxPortLoopbackConfig.name: atmxPortLoopbackConfig
atmxPortLoopbackConfig.description: Loopback config. for this physical layer. 1 = NoLoop, 2 = DiagLoop, 3 = LineLoop, 4 = CellLoop, 5 = PayloadLoop

atmxPortSSCOPstatus.name: atmxPortSSCOPstatus
atmxPortSSCOPstatus.description: SSCOP status of this physical layer.

atmxPortILMIstatus.name: atmxPortILMIstatus
atmxPortILMIstatus.description: ILMI status of this physical layer.

atmxServiceTable.description: A table of ATM services status and parameter information.

atmxServiceEntry.name: atmxServiceEntry
atmxServiceEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the ATM services.

atmxServiceSlotIndex.name: atmxServiceSlotIndex
atmxServiceSlotIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this hsm board slot.

atmxServicePortIndex.name: atmxServicePortIndex
atmxServicePortIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this atm submodule port.

atmxServiceNumber.name: atmxServiceNumber
atmxServiceNumber.description: The unique service number for this particular slot/port.

atmxServiceDescription.name: atmxServiceDescription
atmxServiceDescription.description: A description for this atm service.

atmxServiceType.name: atmxServiceType
atmxServiceType.description: The service type. For 1483 Scaling Service, create it only with 1 group and 1 vc thru this atmxServiceGroup. Adding Other group-to-vc mapping should utilize the atmx1483ScaleGroup.

atmxServiceConnectionType.name: atmxServiceConnectionType
atmxServiceConnectionType.description: The connection type of this board.

atmxServiceEncapsType.name: atmxServiceEncapsType
atmxServiceEncapsType.description: The service encapsulation type. This object is applicable only to PTOP service.

atmxServiceArpRequestServer.name: atmxServiceArpRequestServer
atmxServiceArpRequestServer.description: The Arp request server. 0 = not applicable, 1 = Non arp server, 2 = arp server.

atmxServiceConnections.name: atmxServiceConnections
atmxServiceConnections.description: The connections for this service. Interpret this as a 16 bit field per connection: Trunking 1, PTOP Bridging 1, Classical IP 1..255. For Vlan cluster, this object is interpreted as a 32 bit field where each 32 bit represent the vci value of the Data Direct vcc and the Multicast In vcc. Each vcc take up 16 bits. There can be up to 32 pairs of Data Direct vcc and Mulitcast In vcc. For 1483 Scaling Service, create it only with 1 group and 1 vc thru this atmxServiceGroup. Adding Other group-to-vc mapping should utilize the atmx1483ScaleGroup.

atmxServiceAddresses.name: atmxServiceAddresses
atmxServiceAddresses.description: The addresses for this service. Interpret this as a 16 bit field per address: Trunking 1, PTOP Bridging 1, Classical IP 1..255.

atmxServiceVlan.name: atmxServiceVlan
atmxServiceVlan.description: The Vlans for this service. Interpret this as a 16 bit field per vlan: Trunking 1-32, PTOP Bridging 1, Classical IP 1. For Vlan Cluster, it will depend on the encapsulation type selected. If RFC 1483, only 1 vlan while Xylan ATM trunking up to 32 vlans are allowed. For 1483 Scaling Service, create it only with 1 group and 1 vc thru this atmxServiceGroup. Adding Other group-to-vc mapping should utilize the atmx1483ScaleGroup.

atmxServiceSEL.name: atmxServiceSEL
atmxServiceSEL.description: The SEL for the ATM address of this service.

atmxServiceLaneCfgTblIdx.name: atmxServiceLaneCfgTblIdx
atmxServiceLaneCfgTblIdx.description: Index to the LAN Emulation Configuration Table. This index is only used when the Service type is ATM LAN Emulation. For other service type this should be set to zero (0).

atmxServiceMulticastOutVcc.name: atmxServiceMulticastOutVcc
atmxServiceMulticastOutVcc.description: The Multicast Out VCC for this Vlan Cluster (X-LANE) service. This is only applicable to service type Vlan Cluster. For other ATM services, this object will return a zero (0). For Vlan Cluster service if a zero (0) is returned means no Multicast out is specified.

atmxServiceNumVclMembers.name: atmxServiceNumVclMembers
atmxServiceNumVclMembers.description: The number of other Vlan cluster members defined and have a data direct VCC associated with the connection. This object is valid only for Vlan cluster services. Zero (0) will be returned for other ATM services.

atmxServiceVclEncapType.name: atmxServiceVclEncapType
atmxServiceVclEncapType.description: The Encapsulation type for the Vlan Cluster service. 1 = RFC 1483 encapsulation. 2 = Xylan ATM trunking. 3 = not applicable. This object is only valid for Vlan cluster services. All other ATM services will return a value of 3. If the encapsulation type is RFC 1483, only one (1) vlan as defined in atmxServiceVlan can be associated with this service. If encapsulation type is Xylan ATM trunking more than 1 vlan can be assocated with this service.

atmxServiceSahiBwgNum.name: atmxServiceSahiBwgNum
atmxServiceSahiBwgNum.description: The bwg num for sahi based hsm's. The user can set the pcr, scr, mbs using the bwg table and chose the desired bwg num for this service ensuring that this service obtains the desired bandwidth

atmLecConfigTable.name: atmLecConfigTable
atmLecConfigTable.description: This table contains all the configuration parameters for a LAN Emulation client.

atmLecConfigEntry.name: atmLecConfigEntry
atmLecConfigEntry.description: Each table entry contains configuration information for one LAN Emulation Client. Most of the objects are derived from Initial State Parameters in the LAN Emulation specification.

atmxLecConfigIndex.name: atmxLecConfigIndex
atmxLecConfigIndex.description: Index to identify an instance of this table.

atmLecConfigLecsAtmAddress.name: atmLecConfigLecsAtmAddress
atmLecConfigLecsAtmAddress.description: The LAN Emulation Configuration Server which this client can use if the Well Known LECS address is not used.

atmLecConfigUseDefaultLecsAddr.name: atmLecConfigUseDefaultLecsAddr
atmLecConfigUseDefaultLecsAddr.description: This is to specify if this client is to use the Well Know LECS address or user supplied address. This object alone with atmLecConfigLecsAtmAddress is meaningless if the atmLecConfigMode is setted to manual(2) mode. 1 = TRUE 2 = FALSE

atmLecRowStatus.name: atmLecRowStatus
atmLecRowStatus.description: This object lets network managers create and delete an instance for this table. 1 = Create, 2 = Delete, 3 = Modify.

atmLecRowInUse.name: atmLecRowInUse
atmLecRowInUse.description: This object returns a value to indicate if this instance is used by an ATM service. 1 = In use 2 = Free.

atmLecConfigMode.name: atmLecConfigMode
atmLecConfigMode.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Sections 3.4.1.1 and 5.3
atmLecConfigMode.description: Indicates whether this LAN Emulation Client should auto-configure the next time it is (re)started. In automatic(1) mode, a client uses a LAN Emulation Configuration Server to learn the ATM address of its LAN Emulation Server, and to obtain other parameters. atmLecConfig{ LanType, MaxDataFrameSize, LanName } are used in the Configure request. atmLecConfigLesAtmAddress is ignored. In manual(2) mode, management tells the client the ATM address of its LAN Emulation Server and the values of other parameters. atmLecConfig{ LanType, MaxDataFrameSize, LanName } are used in the Join request. atmLecConfigLesAtmAddress tells the client which LES to call.

atmLecConfigLanType.name: atmLecConfigLanType
atmLecConfigLanType.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecConfigLanType.description: C2 LAN Type. The data frame format which this client will use the next time it returns to the Initial State. Auto-configuring clients use this parameter in their Configure requests. Manually-configured clients use it in their Join requests. This MIB object will not be overwritten with the new value from a LE_{JOIN,CONFIGURE}_RESPONSE. Instead, atmLecActualLanType will be.

atmLecConfigMaxDataFrameSize.name: atmLecConfigMaxDataFrameSize
atmLecConfigMaxDataFrameSize.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecConfigMaxDataFrameSize.description: C3 Maximum Data Frame Size. The maximum data frame size which this client will use the next time it returns to the Initial State. Auto-configuring clients use this parameter in their Configure requests. Manually-configured clients use it in their Join requests. This MIB object will not be overwritten with the new value from a LE_{JOIN,CONFIGURE}_RESPONSE. Instead, atmLecActualMaxDataFrameSize will be.

atmLecConfigLanName.name: atmLecConfigLanName
atmLecConfigLanName.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecConfigLanName.description: C5 ELAN Name. The ELAN Name this client will use the next time it returns to the Initial State. Auto-configuring clients use this parameter in their Configure requests. Manually-configured clients use it in their Join requests. This MIB object will not be overwritten with the new value from a LE_{JOIN,CONFIGURE}_RESPONSE. Instead, atmLecActualLanName will be.

atmLecConfigLesAtmAddress.name: atmLecConfigLesAtmAddress
atmLecConfigLesAtmAddress.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecConfigLesAtmAddress.description: C9 LE Server ATM Address. The LAN Emulation Server which this client will use the next time it is started in manual configuration mode. When atmLecConfigMode is 'automatic', there is no need to set this address, and no advantage to doing so. The client will use the LECS to find a LES, putting the auto-configured address in atmLecActualLesAtmAddress while leaving atmLecConfigLesAtmAddress alone.

atmLecControlTimeout.name: atmLecControlTimeout
atmLecControlTimeout.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecControlTimeout.description: C7 Control Time-out. Time out period used for timing out most request/response control frame interactions, as specified elsewhere [in the LAN Emulation specification]. This time value is expressed in seconds.

atmLecMaxUnknownFrameCount.name: atmLecMaxUnknownFrameCount
atmLecMaxUnknownFrameCount.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecMaxUnknownFrameCount.description: C10 Maximum Unknown Frame Count. See the description of atmLecMaxUnknownFrameTime below.

atmLecMaxUnknownFrameTime.name: atmLecMaxUnknownFrameTime
atmLecMaxUnknownFrameTime.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecMaxUnknownFrameTime.description: C11 Maximum Unknown Frame Time. Within the period of time defined by the Maximum Unknown Frame Time, a LE Client will send no more than Maximum Unknown Frame Count frames to the BUS for a given unicast LAN Destination, and it must also initiate the address resolution protocol to resolve that LAN Destination. This time value is expressed in seconds.

atmLecVccTimeoutPeriod.name: atmLecVccTimeoutPeriod
atmLecVccTimeoutPeriod.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecVccTimeoutPeriod.description: C12 VCC Time-out Period. A LE Client SHOULD release any Data Direct VCC that it has not used to transmit or receive any data frames for the length of the VCC Time-out Period. This parameter is only meaningful for SVC Data Direct VCCs. This time value is expressed in seconds. The default value is 20 minutes. A value of 0 seconds means that the timeout period is infinite. Negative values will be rejected by the agent.

atmLecMaxRetryCount.name: atmLecMaxRetryCount
atmLecMaxRetryCount.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecMaxRetryCount.description: C13 Maximum Retry Count. A LE CLient MUST not retry a LE_ARP_REQUEST for a given frame's LAN destination more than Maximum Retry Count times, after the first LE_ARP_REQUEST for that same frame's LAN destination.

atmLecAgingTime.name: atmLecAgingTime
atmLecAgingTime.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecAgingTime.description: C17 Aging Time. The maximum time that a LE Client will maintain an entry in its LE_ARP cache in the absence of a verification of that relationship. This time value is expressed in seconds.

atmLecForwardDelayTime.name: atmLecForwardDelayTime
atmLecForwardDelayTime.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecForwardDelayTime.description: C18 Forward Delay Time. The maximum time that a LE Client will maintain an entry for a non-local MAC address in its LE_ARP cache in the absence of a verification of that relationship, as long as the Topology Change flag C19 is true. atmLecForwardDelayTime SHOULD BE less than atmLecAgingTime. When it is not, atmLecAgingTime governs LE_ARP aging. This time value is expressed in seconds.

atmLecExpectedArpResponseTime.name: atmLecExpectedArpResponseTime
atmLecExpectedArpResponseTime.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecExpectedArpResponseTime.description: C20 Expected LE_ARP Reponse Time. The maximum time that the LEC expects an LE_ARP_REQUEST/ LE_ARP_RESPONSE cycle to take. Used for retries and verifies. This time value is expressed in seconds.

atmLecFlushTimeOut.name: atmLecFlushTimeOut
atmLecFlushTimeOut.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecFlushTimeOut.description: C21 Flush Time-out. Time limit to wait to receive a LE_FLUSH_RESPONSE after the LE_FLUSH_REQUEST has been sent before taking recovery action. This time value is expressed in seconds.

atmLecPathSwitchingDelay.name: atmLecPathSwitchingDelay
atmLecPathSwitchingDelay.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecPathSwitchingDelay.description: C22 Path Switching Delay. The time since sending a frame to the BUS after which the LE Client may assume that the frame has been either discarded or delivered to the recipient. May be used to bypass the Flush protocol. This time value is expressed in seconds.

atmLecUseForwardDelay.name: atmLecUseForwardDelay
atmLecUseForwardDelay.description: This is specify whether to use Forward delay or arp cache aging time 1 = No, 2 = Yes.

atmLecUseTranslation.name: atmLecUseTranslation
atmLecUseTranslation.description: Use translation option or not. If set to yes, user must set the translation options by the swch command in UI or the vportSwitchTable to set the translation option other than the default defined for LANE. 1 = no, 2 = yes.

atmLecSrBridgeNum.name: atmLecSrBridgeNum
atmLecSrBridgeNum.description: SR bridge number for the LEC

atmLecSrRingNum.name: atmLecSrRingNum
atmLecSrRingNum.description: SR Ring number for the LEC

atmLecStatusTable.name: atmLecStatusTable
atmLecStatusTable.description: A read-only table containing identification, status, and operational information about the LAN Emulation Clients this agent manages.

atmLecStatusEntry.name: atmLecStatusEntry
atmLecStatusEntry.description: Each table entry contains information about one LAN Emulation Client.

atmxLecStatusSlotIndex.name: atmxLecStatusSlotIndex
atmxLecStatusSlotIndex.description: Slot index to identify an instance of this table.

atmxLecStatusPortIndex.name: atmxLecStatusPortIndex
atmxLecStatusPortIndex.description: Port index to identify an instance of this table.

atmxLecStatusServiceNum.name: atmxLecStatusServiceNum
atmxLecStatusServiceNum.description: Service number index to identify an instance of this table.

atmLecPrimaryAtmAddress.name: atmLecPrimaryAtmAddress
atmLecPrimaryAtmAddress.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecPrimaryAtmAddress.description: C1 LE Client's ATM Addresses. The primary ATM address of this LAN Emulation Client. This address is used to establish the Control Direct and Multicast Send VCCs, and may also be used to set up Data Direct VCCs. A client may have additional ATM addresses for use with Data Direct VCCs. These addresses are readable via the atmLecAtmAddressTable.

atmLecID.name: atmLecID
atmLecID.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecID.description: C14 LE Client Identifier. Each LE Client requires a LE Client Identifier (LECID) assigned by the LE Server during the Join phase. The LECID is placed in control requests by the LE Client and MAY be used for echo suppression on multicast data frames sent by that LE Client. This value MUST NOT change without terminating the LE Client and returning to the Initial state. A valid LECID MUST be in the range X'0001' through X'FEFF'. The value of this object is only meaningful for a LEC that is connected to a LES. For a LEC which does not belong to an emulated LAN, the value of this object is defined to be 0.

atmLecInterfaceState.name: atmLecInterfaceState
atmLecInterfaceState.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 2.3.1
atmLecInterfaceState.description: The mandatory state of the LAN Emulation Client. Note that 'ifOperStatus' is defined to be 'up' when, and only when, 'atmLecInterfaceState' is 'operational'.

atmLecLastFailureRespCode.name: atmLecLastFailureRespCode
atmLecLastFailureRespCode.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 4.2, Table 13
atmLecLastFailureRespCode.description: Status code from the last failed Configure response or Join response. Failed responses are those for which the LE_CONFIGURE_RESPONSE / LE_JOIN_RESPONSE frame contains a non-zero code, or fails to arrive within a timeout period. If none of this client's requests have failed, this object has the value 'none'. If the failed response contained a STATUS code that is not defined in the LAN Emulation specification, this object has the value 'undefinedError'. The value 'timeout' is self-explanatory. Other failure codes correspond to those defined in the specification, although they may have different numeric values.

atmLecLastFailureState.name: atmLecLastFailureState
atmLecLastFailureState.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 2.3.1
atmLecLastFailureState.description: The state this client was in when it updated the 'atmLecLastFailureRespCode'. If 'atmLecLastFailureRespCode' is 'none', this object has the value initialState(1).

atmLecProtocol.name: atmLecProtocol
atmLecProtocol.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 4.2
atmLecProtocol.description: The LAN Emulation protocol which this client supports, and specifies in its LE_JOIN_REQUESTs.

atmLecVersion.name: atmLecVersion
atmLecVersion.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 4.2
atmLecVersion.description: The LAN Emulation protocol version which this client supports, and specifies in its LE_JOIN_REQUESTs.

atmLecTopologyChange.name: atmLecTopologyChange
atmLecTopologyChange.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecTopologyChange.description: C19 Topology Change. Boolean indication that the LE Client is using the Forward Delay Time C18, instead of the Aging Time C17, to age non-local entries in its LE_ARP cache C16. For a client which is not connected to the LES, this object is defined to have the value 'false'.

atmLecConfigServerAtmAddress.name: atmLecConfigServerAtmAddress
atmLecConfigServerAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of the LAN Emulation Configuration Server (if known) or the empty string (otherwise).

atmLecConfigSource.name: atmLecConfigSource
atmLecConfigSource.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.2
atmLecConfigSource.description: Indicates whether this LAN Emulation Client used the LAN Emulation Configuration Server, and, if so, what method it used to establish the Configuration Direct VCC.

atmLecActualLanType.name: atmLecActualLanType
atmLecActualLanType.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecActualLanType.description: C2 LAN Type. The data frame format that this LAN Emulation Client is using right now. This may come from * atmLecConfigLanType, * the LAN Emulation Configuration Server, or * the LAN Emulation Server This value is related to 'ifMtu' and 'ifType'. See the LEC management specification for more details.

atmLecActualMaxDataFrameSize.name: atmLecActualMaxDataFrameSize
atmLecActualMaxDataFrameSize.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecActualMaxDataFrameSize.description: C3 Maximum Data Frame Size. The maximum data frame size that this LAN Emulation client is using right now. This may come from * atmLecConfigMaxDataFrameSize, * the LAN Emulation Configuration Server, or * the LAN Emulation Server

atmLecActualLanName.name: atmLecActualLanName
atmLecActualLanName.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecActualLanName.description: C5 ELAN Name. The identity of the emulated LAN which this client last joined, or wishes to join. This may come from * atmLecConfigLanName, * the LAN Emulation Configuration Server, or * the LAN Emulation Server

atmLecActualLesAtmAddress.name: atmLecActualLesAtmAddress
atmLecActualLesAtmAddress.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecActualLesAtmAddress.description: C9 LE Server ATM Address. The LAN Emulation Server address currently in use or most recently attempted. If no LAN Emulation Server attachment has been tried, this object's value is the zero-length string.

atmLecProxyClient.name: atmLecProxyClient
atmLecProxyClient.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 5.1.1
atmLecProxyClient.description: C4 Proxy. Indicates whether this client is acting as a proxy. Proxy clients are allowed to represent unregistered MAC addresses, and receive copies of LE_ARP_REQUEST frames for such addresses.

atmLecStatisticsTable.name: atmLecStatisticsTable
atmLecStatisticsTable.description: An extension table containing traffic statistics for all the LAN Emulation Clients this host implements.

atmLecStatisticsEntry.name: atmLecStatisticsEntry
atmLecStatisticsEntry.description: Each row in this table contains traffic statistics for one LAN Emulation client.

atmxLecStatsSlotIndex.name: atmxLecStatsSlotIndex
atmxLecStatsSlotIndex.description: Slot index to identify an instance of this table.

atmxLecStatsPortIndex.name: atmxLecStatsPortIndex
atmxLecStatsPortIndex.description: Port index to identify an instance of this table.

atmxLecStatsServiceNum.name: atmxLecStatsServiceNum
atmxLecStatsServiceNum.description: Service number index to identify an instance of this table.

atmLecArpRequestsOut.name: atmLecArpRequestsOut
atmLecArpRequestsOut.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs sent over the LUNI by this LAN Emulation Client.

atmLecArpRequestsIn.name: atmLecArpRequestsIn
atmLecArpRequestsIn.description: The number of LE_ARP_REQUESTs received over the LUNI by this LAN Emulation Client. Requests may arrive on the Control Direct VCC or on the Control Distribute VCC, depending upon how the LES is implemented and the chances it has had for learning. This counter covers both VCCs.

atmLecArpRepliesOut.name: atmLecArpRepliesOut
atmLecArpRepliesOut.description: The number of LE_ARP_RESPONSEs sent over the LUNI by this LAN Emulation Client.

atmLecArpRepliesIn.name: atmLecArpRepliesIn
atmLecArpRepliesIn.description: The number of LE_ARP_RESPONSEs received over the LUNI by this LAN Emulation Client. This count includes all such replies, whether solicited or not. Replies may arrive on the Control Direct VCC or on the Control Distribute VCC, depending upon how the LES is implemented. This counter covers both VCCs.

atmLecControlFramesOut.name: atmLecControlFramesOut
atmLecControlFramesOut.description: The total number of control packets sent by this LAN Emulation Client over the LUNI.

atmLecControlFramesIn.name: atmLecControlFramesIn
atmLecControlFramesIn.description: The total number of control packets received by this LAN Emulation Client over the LUNI.

atmLecSvcFailures.name: atmLecSvcFailures
atmLecSvcFailures.description: The total number of * outgoing LAN Emulation SVCs which this client tried, but failed, to open; * incoming LAN Emulation SVCs which this client tried, but failed to establish; and * incoming LAN Emulation SVCs which this client rejected for protocol or security reasons.

atmLecServerVccTable.name: atmLecServerVccTable
atmLecServerVccTable.description: A table identifying the Control and Multicast VCCs for each LAN Emulation Client this host implements.

atmLecServerVccEntry.name: atmLecServerVccEntry
atmLecServerVccEntry.description: Each row in this table describes the Control VCCs and Multicast VCCs for one LAN Emulation client.

atmxLecSlotIndex.name: atmxLecSlotIndex
atmxLecSlotIndex.description: index that uniquely identify an instance of the atmLecServerVccTable.

atmxLecPortIndex.name: atmxLecPortIndex
atmxLecPortIndex.description: index that uniquely identify an instance of the atmLecServerVccTable.

atmxLecServiceNum.name: atmxLecServiceNum
atmxLecServiceNum.description: Index that uniquely identify an instance of the atmLecServerVccTable.

atmLecConfigDirectVpi.name: atmLecConfigDirectVpi
atmLecConfigDirectVpi.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 2.2.2.1.1
atmLecConfigDirectVpi.description: If the Configuration Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VPI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

atmLecConfigDirectVci.name: atmLecConfigDirectVci
atmLecConfigDirectVci.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 2.2.2.1.1
atmLecConfigDirectVci.description: If the Configuration Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VCI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

atmLecControlDirectVpi.name: atmLecControlDirectVpi
atmLecControlDirectVpi.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 2.2.2.1.2
atmLecControlDirectVpi.description: If the Control Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VPI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

atmLecControlDirectVci.name: atmLecControlDirectVci
atmLecControlDirectVci.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 2.2.2.1.2
atmLecControlDirectVci.description: If the Control Direct VCC exists, this object contains the VCI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

atmLecControlDistributeVpi.name: atmLecControlDistributeVpi
atmLecControlDistributeVpi.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 2.2.2.1.3
atmLecControlDistributeVpi.description: If the Control Distribute VCC exists, this object contains the VPI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

atmLecControlDistributeVci.name: atmLecControlDistributeVci
atmLecControlDistributeVci.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 2.2.2.1.3
atmLecControlDistributeVci.description: If the Control Distribute VCC exists, this object contains the VCI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object contains the value 0.

atmLecMulticastSendVpi.name: atmLecMulticastSendVpi
atmLecMulticastSendVpi.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, V1.0, Section 2.2.2.2.2
atmLecMulticastSendVpi.description: If the Multicast Send VCC exists, this object contains the VPI which identifies that VCC at the point where it connects to this LE client. Otherwise, this object has the value 0.

atmLeArpTable.name: atmLeArpTable
atmLeArpTable.reference: ATM Forum LAN Emulation Over ATM Specification, Section 5.1.1
atmLeArpTable.description: This table provides access to an ATM LAN Emulation Client's MAC-to-ATM ARP cache. It contains entries for unicast addresses and for the broadcast address, but not for multicast MAC addresses. C16 LE_ARP Cache. A table of entries, each of which establishes a relationship between a LAN Destination external to the LE Client and the ATM address to which data frames for that LAN Destination will be sent.

atmLeArpMacAddress.name: atmLeArpMacAddress
atmLeArpMacAddress.description: The MAC address for which this cache entry provides a translation. Since ATM LAN Emulation uses an ARP protocol to locate the Broadcast and Unknown Server, the value of this object could be the broadcast MAC address. MAC addresses should be unique within any given ATM Emulated LAN. However, there's no requirement that they be unique across disjoint emulated LANs.

atmLeArpAtmAddress.name: atmLeArpAtmAddress
atmLeArpAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of the Broadcast & Unknown Server or LAN Emulation Client whose MAC address is stored in 'atmLeArpMacAddress'. This value may be determined through the use of the LE_ARP procedure, through source address learning, or through other mechanisms. Some agents may provide write access to this object, as part of their support for 'static' LE_ARP entries. The effect of attempting to write an ATM address to a 'learned' row is explicitly undefined. Agents may disallow the write, accept the write and change the row's type, or even accept the write as-is.

atmLeArpIsRemoteAddress.name: atmLeArpIsRemoteAddress
atmLeArpIsRemoteAddress.description: Indicates whether this entry is for a local or remote MAC address. In this context, 'local' means 'a MAC address that is local to the remote client', as opposed to 'one of my addresses'. true(1) The address is believed to be remote - or its local/remote status is unknown. For an entry created via the LE_ARP mechanism, this corresponds to the 'Remote address' flag being set in the LE_ARP_RESPONSE. During Topology Change periods, remote LE_ARP entries generally age out faster than others. Specifically, they are subject to the Forward Delay Time as well as to the Aging Time. false(2) The address is believed to be local - that is to say, registered with the LES by the client whose ATM address is atmLeArpAtmAddress. For an entry created via the LE_ARP mechanism, this corresponds to the 'Remote address' flag being cleared in the LE_ARP_RESPONSE.
